

##### Rich User Context MEGA-QUERY Pattern

  - a powerful Neo4j optimization that transforms how SKUEL fetches user data.

  What I Built

  Phase 1: Entity-Level Rich Context (from earlier)
  - Added get_with_context() methods to KuCoreService, TasksCoreService, GoalsCoreService
  - Each fetches entity + complete graph neighborhood in 1 query instead of 3-4

  Phase 2: User-Level Rich Context (just completed)
  - Added 9 rich entity fields to UnifiedUserContext (full entities + graph neighborhoods)
  - Created MEGA-QUERY (237 lines) that fetches ALL user data in ONE database round-trip
  - Implemented get_rich_unified_context() in UserService as the orchestration method
  - Created comprehensive integration tests
  - Documented the pattern in CLAUDE.md with examples and architecture diagrams

  Performance Impact

  Before: 50-100 database queries to build a user dashboard
  - Standard context: 5-9 queries
  - Rich entity data: 1 query per task/goal/knowledge/event
  - Total: ~50-100 round-trips for realistic user

  After: 1 MEGA-QUERY
  - Fetches ALL tasks, goals, knowledge, events with complete graph neighborhoods
  - Includes cross-domain insights (task→goal alignments, knowledge applications)
  - 50-100x query reduction!

