  Key Features

  ✅ Dual Context Model - Standard (UIDs only) + Rich (full entities + graph)
  ✅ MEGA-QUERY - Single comprehensive Cypher query fetches everything
  ✅ Cross-Domain Insights - Extracts task→goal, knowledge→task, principle→goal patterns
  ✅ Graceful Degradation - Handles empty users without errors
  ✅ Type-Safe - Full Result[T] pattern with proper error handling

  Usage Example

  # Get complete user state with ALL graph neighborhoods
  result = await user_service.get_rich_unified_context(user_uid)
  context = result.value

  # Access lightweight UIDs
  task_uids = context.active_task_uids

  # Access rich entities with full graph context
  for task_data in context.active_tasks_rich:
      task = task_data["task"]
      graph = task_data["graph_context"]

      # Use complete neighborhood data
      subtasks = graph["subtasks"]
      dependencies = graph["dependencies"]
      applied_knowledge = graph["applied_knowledge"]
      goal_context = graph["goal_context"]

